a teórico, las aportaciones del enfoque filológico a cada una de las ramas de la ciencia de la literatura; y, por otro, a analizar un aspecto no lo suficientemente considerado hasta el momento: la materialidad de los archivos literarios, a partir del estudio de los casos concretos de Fernando Pessoa, Miguel de Unamuno, Gabriela Mistral, Federico García Lorca y Carmen Conde.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Spanish, Castilian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLatin American poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh1 aBroullón-Lozano, Manuel A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastillo, Yenny Ariz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcerá, Fran, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez Deyros, María, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez Deyros, María, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPintacuda, Paolo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPizarro, Jerónimo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVeny-Mesquida, Joan Ramon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertVervuert Complete eBook-Package 2023z9783110998719oZDB-207-IBV40uhttps://doi.org/10.31819/978396869462740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783968694627423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783968694627/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-207-IBVb2023